Together, they imagined\na world in which
nightmares and humans\nlived side by side.
From then on,\nthe country was able to
coexist with some nightmares.
But the conflict\nwas far from over.
A war broke out\nover territory.
The next threat would\nbe the humans themselves.
The kind king hated war\nand went to meet with
the nightmare nation\nto discuss solutions.
As moonlight shone\nover the royal castle,
the king made a pact with\nthe nightmare that night.
He would stop the war and return.
He asked the nightmare\nto defend the castle until then.
The nightmare\ndidn't even blink.
But the king could see\nwhat resembled a nod.
The next day, after seeing the king off,
a visitor appeared\nbefore the nightmare.
The man seemed\nto know the exact time
that the king would\nbe absent.
He had come to\ngive the nightmare
shiny crystallized desires.\n
The nightmare tasted\nthe crystallized desires
that the man was so eager\nto hand over.
When it did,\nthe nightmare's eyes went bright,
and it lost consciousness.
How much time\nhad passed?
The next thing\nthe nightmare saw
was a castle in ruins\nand human bodies piled high.
Reaching out from\nthe pile was a hand
with a jeweled ring\nthat resembled
that of the dear king\nwho had stroked his head...
From that day on,\nthe nightmare guarded the castle.
It was his way of apologizing\nfor not keepin' his word.
And he would do so\nforever and ever...
